				<div class="box">
			<h3>Editorial comment</h3>
			<p>The growing pressure on the EC over its conduct of the Mercosur negotiations may make itself felt in ways which carry important implications for ACP exporters, namely through its impact on the stricter implementation of EU SPS and food-safety regulations. Given that the debate in the European Parliament related to all trade agreements, a more generalised stricter application of EU standards could pose particular challenges for ACP exporters, given the more limited implementation capacities available in ACP countries to ensure that EU SPS, food-safety and quality standards are fully respected.</p><p>This suggests a need to pay careful attention to the scope of SPS-related provisions included in EPAs, to ensure that they establish operationally effective cooperation arrangements which enhance the capacity of ACP authorities to understand EU requirements and also provide the necessary financial support instruments to allow ACP authorities to promote full compliance with EU requirements.</p>
		</div>
		
